<article>
    <h1>COVID-19 CURBS EASED</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200924/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-24"><time>2020-09-24</time></a>
        - <span>FRONT PAGE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• More staff can work from of­fice from Sept 28</p>
    <p>• Work­place events al­lowed to re­sume in of­fice, for up to 50 peo­ple</p>
    <p>• Chil­dren be­low six no longer have to wear masks from</p>
    <p>Sept 28</p>
    <p>• Grad­ual ex­pan­sion of cin­ema ca­pac­i­ties from Oct 1</p>
    <p>• Up to 100 peo­ple will be al­lowed for wor­ship ser­vices and wed­dings from Oct 3</p>
    <p>• Pi­lot scheme to al­low es­sen­tial busi­ness travel for se­nior ex­ec­u­tives</p>
    <p>Covid-19 safety mea­sures here are be­ing re­laxed sig­nif­i­cantly as Sin­ga­pore re­opens the econ­omy fur­ther, amid low com­mu­nity case num­bers.</p>
    <p>Clara Chong re­ports on the changes.</p>
    <p>BACK TO WORK</p>
    <p>Work­ing from home re­mains the de­fault, but from next Mon­day, more em­ploy­ees who can work from home can opt to re­turn, pro­vided: They con­tinue to work from home for at least half their work­ing time. Fewer than half of a firm’s em­ploy­ees are at the work­place at any point. Work­ers have flex­i­ble work­ing hours to min­imise crowd­ing. Re­port­ing times are stag­gered, with half of all em­ploy­ees start­ing work at 10am or later. Split team or shift ar­range­ments con­tinue. Events at the of­fice or work­place</p>
    <p>Work-re­lated events of up to</p>
    <p>50</p>
    <p>peo­ple, de­pend­ing on venue ca­pac­ity, are al­lowed. Larger-scale so­cial gath­er­ings within or out­side the work­place re­main off the ta­ble.</p>

